text:
Sharing this mostly for <@U02F8LF2X>'s benefit but thought other Italian aficionados may appreciate it. My daughter and I just crashed what we thought was an Italian meetup at the park but ended up being an large Italian-American family picnic. Turns out they're all descendants from a family of 5 Italian body-builder brothers who emigrated to America around 1940. Fun!

Italians are so friendly, they kept asking me to stay for lunch and show up to their Wednesday family gatherings.
OH from a 13 y/o: "we used to be BFFs but then she dropped me like last year's phone"
